---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Kat Bella - Now">
  <section>
    <h1>Now</h1>
    <p>
      After spending the last few years working on an ambitious game project,
      I'm focused on smaller projects that let me put creativity first and build
      things other people can use and enjoy.
    </p>

    <h2>Doodle Engine</h2>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://doodleengine.dev"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">Doodle Engine</a
      > is one of the projects I'm most excited about right now. It's my way of revisiting
      the story-driven side of the Infinity Engine games that first got me into making
      games, while also building something that's useful and fun to use. It's a TypeScript
      library for narrative games, with a dialogue and quest system I've tried to
      keep approachable for both developers and writers.
    </p>

    <h2>Music</h2>
    <p>
      I've also been spending more time on music again. It's been a while since
      I've worked actively on a music project, but I've been experimenting with
      new sounds and ideas, especially around Nordic folk music, nature-inspired
      themes, and some of the synth-heavy sounds I still really enjoy. I may
      share a track or two here in the future.
    </p>

    <small class="updated">updated march 2026</small>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-block: 1.5rem 1rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  p a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.12em;
    text-decoration-thickness: 0.08em;
  }

  .updated {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
</style>
